body:
What do you think about wrapping the code with `zmq` namespace and removing `ZMQ/zmq` prefix from class/function names? 
Basically when the location of the file is `a/b/c.cpp` then we have:
```c++
namespace a {
namespace b {
class C {}
}
}
```

